~PR~
Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this chemical sunscreen from Kopari today!
üîÜ
- UV Filters: Homosalate, Octisalate, Octocrylene, and Avobenzone
- It has a gel texture
- No white cast on my skin tone¬†
- I notice a bit of residue in my facial hair
- Has a satin matte finish
- No added fragrance and essential oils
- Doesn't sting my eyes
- Around 10-12 pumps to get the necessary amount needed for proper protection (around 1/2 teaspoon for face/neck)
- Around $38 for 44mL. Can be purchased from their website or retailers like Sephora.
üîÜ
I was really intruiged by the finish of this one, very interesting. It is satin matte but it is made to give a glow. It has pearlescent minerals in it to give a subtle glow even though it as a whole is satin matte. I could feel the residue throughout the day anytime I touched my facial hair, and the pearlescent minerals for the glow were making my facial hair look a little gray to me. So I liked the finish, but this one is not the perfect one for me. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

text:
Foundation looking cakey? Here‚Äôs how to fix it with a few key tweaks:
(Save so you can come back to this)
1. Choose the Right Foundation for Your Skin Type:
Many people gravitate toward full-coverage foundations to cover skin concerns. However, full-coverage formulas are often rich in texture and matte, making them prone to looking cakey. Matte, full-coverage foundations can work well for oily skin, as they tend to last longer, but those with dry skin should avoid them. Personally, I recommend a medium-coverage foundation with a satin finish for any skin type. They‚Äôre buildable, offer great coverage, and suit all skin types. For oilier skin, using a quality setting powder and spray can help maintain a flawless base.

2. Adjust Skin Prep with the Seasons:
It‚Äôs essential to tailor your skin prep to your skin type and to the weather. In winter, for example, try adding a drop of your favorite face oil or moisturizer to your foundation to avoid it looking too cakey. A little seasonal adjustment goes a long way!

3. Choose Your Application Tools Wisely:
I like to use a mix of brushes, powder puffs, and sponges to achieve a smooth finish. Start by picking up minimal product with a brush and build coverage only where needed. After applying with a brush, go over the foundation with a lightly damp sponge to remove any excess product, blend edges, and smooth out the application.

4. Use Setting Spray Between Layers:
For fuller coverage, try misting setting spray between layers and then blending lightly with a sponge. This helps your foundation look fresh and extends its wear.

5. Avoid Overdoing Powder:
Setting powders are great for keeping oily areas in check, but overusing powder can make makeup look crusty and cakey. Always tap off excess powder from your brush or puff before applying to prevent buildup.

6. Be Patient and Embrace Your Skin‚Äôs Uniqueness:
Makeup is a skill that takes practice and experimenting with tools, techniques, and products. Be patient, and don‚Äôt expect perfection right away. Also, remember that real skin has texture, pores, and imperfections. Don‚Äôt compare yourself to the filtered, edited images you see online. Embrace your natural beauty!

text:
Looking for a super affordable, cushiony liquid lip balm? I‚Äôve got you!

The Lilybyred Tangle Jelly Balms are $9.79 on YesStyle 

Key ingredients: Hydrolyzed Collagen, Mango Seed Oil, Grape Seed Oil, Apricot Seed Oil and Passion Fruit Seed Oil.

Formula: a liquid lip balm with a glossy finish, and a cushiony, thick texture. It does feel a little oily on the lips, especially when the color wears off, but it‚Äôs not slippery. It‚Äôs ever-so-slightly sticky so if you want something that lasts a little longer than a lip oil, you‚Äôll like these. On the lips, they feel similarly to the Naturium phyto glow lip balms.

Finish: it has a slightly smoothing finish if you apply a good amount!

Packaging: this is where the product misses for me. The packaging is SO STIFF and difficult to squeeze, I genuinely have to squeeze it with two hands. I also don‚Äôt like that it‚Äôs in a squeezey tube because I find the it can get a bit messy when applying the product. If this had been in packaging with a wand I would‚Äôve much preferred it, but for $9 I can‚Äôt complain.

Scent: it has an artificial apricot scent, definitely not my favorite because it smells quite chemically but it does disappear quickly.

Overall, I LOVE the formula, finish, colors, and pricepoint of these lip balms. State of Kait approved!

What do you think? Would you try these? .

text:
‚ú® Pore Blurring Experience with a Makeup Base - tfit Delicate Silk Veil Art Primer ‚ú®

Thanks to @tfit.global for sending me this makeup primer for review. I‚Äôve been using it for almost 2 weeks and I LOVE it!

Product Claims:

üå∏ Pore-Blurring Magic: Say goodbye to visible pores and hello to a smooth, airbrushed finish! This primer instantly minimizes pores, fine lines, and uneven texture for the perfect base.

üåü Smooth & Lightweight: The product has a silky, lightweight texture that feels like a second skin. It‚Äôs breathable without any greasiness.

üíñ Brighten with Pink Tint: The delicate pink tint enhances your skin complexion.

üí¶ Water & Sweat Proof: Stay flawless all day long! This primer is resistant to water and sweat, keeping makeup intact in any condition.

üíÑ 12-Hour Freshness: Lock in your makeup for up to 12 hours without smudging or caking. Keep your makeup looking fresh and flawless all day.

What do I think about it?

‚úÖ It doesn‚Äôt break me out or create a rubbery residue when I apply face powder or foundation on top of it.

‚úÖ It blurs my pores and makes them less visible.

‚úÖ The pink tint is a plus as it brightens my yellowish skin complexion, just as the product claims.

‚úÖ It doesn‚Äôt burn my eyes.

I live in Hong Kong, so the weather is hot üî• and humid üí¶. Under these conditions, I don‚Äôt think this primer can keep my makeup fresh for 12 hours, as my sebum and sweat oxidize the foundation and probably the makeup primer. My skin complexion turns ‚Äúyellow‚Äù again, closer to my natural skin tone after a few hours.

It‚Äôs not a typical makeup base that glides on the skin easily ‚Äî I have to squeeze the tube harder to get the product, then tug at my skin and use my fingers to apply the primer upward. These don‚Äôt bother me at all. In fact, this formula is better than a typical spreadable makeup base, which tends to melt and create residues when I put on foundation or touch up during the day.

Have you tried tfit Delicate Silk Veil Art Primer?

text:
Kulfi Beauty sent me their Lassi Lips Staining Long-Lasting Moisturizing Lip Oils and here are my thoughts:

These are $24 each and are described as a ‚Äúsmooth staining lip oil that goes on glossy, leaving a perfectly pigmented stain that lasts with one swipe and won‚Äôt feather, flake, or transfer.‚Äù

These are totally unscented and feel light-as-a-feather on the lips. They‚Äôre definitely unlike any other lip stain I‚Äôve tried, they truly feel weightless, like you‚Äôre just wearing a super light, watery lip oil. The stain they leave behind is even (not patchy) and I think the shade range is nice and balanced with a range for different skin tones.

I wouldn‚Äôt say they‚Äôre moisturizing or provide any long-lasting nourishment, but they are very comfortable and don‚Äôt feel drying.

I do have to warn you, my black cherry leaked from the top all over my desk. When I posted about it on my IG stories, I got quite a few messages from people saying their black cherry also had a defect and leaked from the top.

So I don‚Äôt feel confident saying you should buy the black cherry shade, but I didn‚Äôt have issues with any of the other colors.

Overall, I think these are a really nice launch from Kulfi, especially if you like products that are lightweight! I personally prefer brighter shades for my skin tone so I won‚Äôt be keeping any of these, but I can see a lot of people loving this launch.

Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this chemical sunscreen from Elemis today! 
üîÜ
- UV Filters: Avobenzone, Octisalate, and Octocrylene
- It has a gel cream texture

- Works well in my facial hair

The finish and look throughout the day is lovely. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

text:
~PR~
Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this new chemical sunscreen from Murad today! 
üîÜ
- UV Filters: Avobenzone, Homosalate, Octisalate, and Octocrylene
- It has a clear gel texture
- No white cast on my skin tone
- Works fine in my facial hair
- Has a natural radiant finish
- Has added fragrance and essential oils, but I don't notice much of a scent
- Does not sting my eyes
- Water and sweat resistant
- Around $42 for 50mL. Can be purchased from their retailers like Sephora or their website.
üîÜ
I definitely did not get velvety matte from this. They did mention a few times on their website that this is meant to be nourishing, so maybe it is geared more to those closer to dry skin. I did find it a bit greasy and like it was a layer of slip sitting on my skin. Nice that there is no white cast and it is easy to apply. But definitely not my fave when it comes to this category of siliconey clear gel sunscreens. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

I‚Äôm here to take acne scars down for good ‚Äì and it takes a whole new level of true experience and expertise to make that happen.

When this patient came to me, he was tired of feeling held back by his scars. He‚Äôd tried all literally all of the usual solutions, but they just weren‚Äôt enough. I could tell he needed a high-impact procedure ‚Äì not something one-size-fits-all. So, I got to work, using a unique combination that I‚Äôve refined over years of experience to create the kind of results that turn heads! üòä

Here‚Äôs exactly how I approached his case to tackle his scars from every angle:

‚úÖBellafill ‚Äì a top choice of mine to fill in the deeper scars and restore volume, giving an immediate boost and long-term support as the skin rebuilds.

‚úÖSubcision ‚Äì one of my go-to techniques, where I go under the skin to break up those stubborn, tethered scars. This is critical in allowing the skin to finally smooth out.

‚úÖPixel8 ‚Äì another favorite, to target texture and kickstart collagen production, rebuilding his skin from the inside out.

‚úÖCO2 Resurfacing ‚Äì the final touch, to refine the skin‚Äôs surface and give it that fresh, renewed look.

Going above and beyond is what gives my patients the best possible results. After his session, I applied PRP along with an oxygen facial under red light therapy to kickstart healing and ensure he‚Äôd walk out glowing. Truthfully it‚Äôs all about taking that extra step and going beyond what‚Äôs expected to help patients see a real transformation.

Even after just one round, he is absolutely thrilled with his overall improvement! His friends are asking him about his skin, and he‚Äôs finally seeing what‚Äôs possible with combination treatments. When it comes to scars, I don‚Äôt settle for anything less than life-changing results.

If your acne scars are holding you back, let‚Äôs create a plan to make them a thing of the past.

Let‚Äôs clear this up‚Ä¶

Pores don‚Äôt open or close, and skincare isn‚Äôt one size fits all. Here‚Äôs how to get real about what your skin needs: üí°‚ú®

Oily skin? Look for lightweight, non-comedogenic hydration like gel moisturizers and niacinamide.

Dry skin? Your skin craves ceramides, rich moisturizers, and layers of hydration.

Acne-prone? Don‚Äôt skip SPF (seriously, it matters) and opt for calming ingredients like salicylic acid or azelaic acid.

Combo skin? Customize! A hydrating serum for your cheeks and a mattifying product for your T-zone can work wonders.

Understanding your skin type is the foundation of better results‚Ä¶and your skin will thank you for it. üåøüíï

text:
I bought one new shade of the @tower28beauty oneliner in paint my number and I LOVE it. Here‚Äôs a comparison with Work of Art, my longtime favorite.

If you haven‚Äôt tried the formula they are a classic pencil formula that‚Äôs half creamy, half grippy (but not in a waxy way.) They‚Äôre comfortable and easy to smudge, and they don‚Äôt set down the way, which I prefer.

If you want something super budge proof and transfer resistant, these are not for you. But if you‚Äôre like me and you prefer a more creamy lip liner that isn‚Äôt slippery, I think you‚Äôll love these.

Paint my number is described as a muted mauve but I‚Äôd describe it as a muted rose. It‚Äôs much warmer than what ‚Äúmuted mauve‚Äù would suggest, but I really like it. It goes beautifully with clear gloss, or all of my plum/berry lip glosses.

Work of art is one of my most used liners because it‚Äôs a chameleon. I swear it changes color! Sometimes it looks like a pinky taupe, which is how they describe it, and other times it looks like a warm beige-brown. It‚Äôs perfect for my nude lipsticks but it really seems to go with any gloss I put on top.

Overall, I adore this formula and I really hope Tower 28 continues to launch more shades!

text:
*Korean Glass Skin: The Ultimate Skincare Trend*

Korean beauty (K-beauty) has taken the global beauty industry by storm, and one of its most iconic trends is the concept of "glass skin." Glass skin refers to a complexion that is incredibly smooth, luminous, and translucent, much like a piece of glass. Achieving this flawless, dewy look is the result of meticulous skincare routines designed to nourish, hydrate, and perfect the skin over time.

At the heart of glass skin is the idea of healthy, well-hydrated skin. It‚Äôs not just about masking imperfections or covering up with makeup. Instead, glass skin emphasizes the importance of achieving beauty from within, using a combination of skincare products and techniques that focus on long-term results. The goal is a clear, even-toned complexion that reflects light effortlessly, giving the face a radiant, almost ethereal glow.

The Key Components of a Glass Skin Routine

Achieving glass skin involves a comprehensive skincare regimen, with a focus on hydration, exfoliation, and protection. Here are some key steps:

1. **Double Cleansing**: The first step in the glass skin routine is the K-beauty staple of double cleansing. This process involves using an oil-based cleanser to remove makeup, sunscreen, and impurities, followed by a water-based cleanser to thoroughly clean the skin. Proper cleansing is crucial for preventing breakouts and ensuring that the skin is prepared to absorb subsequent skincare products.

2. **Exfoliation**: Regular exfoliation helps remove dead skin cells, promoting smoother and brighter skin. Gentle exfoliants like AHAs, BHAs, or enzymes work to unclog pores and refine skin texture without causing irritation, which is important for maintaining the smooth, clear base necessary for glass skin.

3. **Toning**: Korean toners are designed to hydrate and balance the skin‚Äôs pH, as well as prepare it to absorb serums and moisturizers. Hydrating toners, often infused with ingredients like hyaluronic acid or rose water, deliver essential moisture to the skin, making it appear plump and fresh.

4. **Essences and Serums**: Essences are lightweight, hydrating liquids that help boost the skin‚Äôs moisture levels. Serums, on the other hand, are more concentrated and are used to target specific skin concerns such as hyperpigmentation, fine lines, or dullness. Layering these products is key to achieving the deep hydration that gives glass skin its signature reflective quality.

5. **Moisturizing**: A rich, hydrating moisturizer seals in all the previous layers of hydration. Look for moisturizers with humectants like glycerin and hyaluronic acid, which draw moisture into the skin, as well as emollients like ceramides and fatty acids to strengthen the skin barrier and lock in moisture.

6. **Sunscreen**: The final step, and perhaps the most important, is applying sunscreen. UV protection is critical to prevent sun damage, which can lead to premature aging and dull skin. Korean sunscreens are often lightweight and formulated to leave the skin looking dewy, adding to the overall glow.

Why Is Glass Skin So Popular?

The appeal of glass skin lies in its emphasis on natural beauty. Unlike makeup-heavy trends, it focuses on achieving a healthy, radiant complexion that doesn‚Äôt rely on cosmetics for coverage. Instead, it encourages a holistic approach to skincare that prioritizes hydration, nourishment, and protection. Moreover, the glow achieved with glass skin makes the face appear youthful, fresh, and vibrant ‚Äî qualities that are universally desired.

Ultimately, glass skin is more than just a trend; it‚Äôs a lifestyle that promotes skincare as a form of self-care, teaching individuals to appreciate the beauty of healthy, well-maintained skin.

text:
‚ú® Pore Blurring Must-Have - tfit Delicate Silk Veil Art Primer ‚ú®

Thanks to @tfit.global for sending me this makeup primer for review. I‚Äôve been using it for almost 2 weeks and I LOVE it!

Product Claims:

üå∏ Pore-Blurring Magic: Say goodbye to visible pores and hello to a smooth, airbrushed finish! This primer instantly minimizes pores, fine lines, and uneven texture for the perfect base.

üåü Smooth & Lightweight: The product has a silky, lightweight texture that feels like a second skin. It‚Äôs breathable without any greasiness.

üíñ Brighten with Pink Tint: The delicate pink tint enhances your skin complexion.

üí¶ Water & Sweat Proof: Stay flawless all day long! This primer is resistant to water and sweat, keeping makeup intact in any condition.

üíÑ 12-Hour Freshness: Lock in your makeup for up to 12 hours without smudging or caking. Keep your makeup looking fresh and flawless all day.

What do I think about it?

‚úÖ It doesn‚Äôt break me out or create a rubbery residue when I apply face powder or foundation on top of it.

‚úÖ It blurs my pores and makes them less visible.

‚úÖ The pink tint is a plus as it brightens my yellowish skin complexion, just as the product claims.

‚úÖ It doesn‚Äôt burn my eyes.

I live in Hong Kong, so the weather is hot üî• and humid üí¶. Under these conditions, I don‚Äôt think this primer can keep my makeup fresh for 12 hours, as my sebum and sweat oxidize the foundation and probably the makeup primer. My skin complexion turns ‚Äúyellow‚Äù again, closer to my natural skin tone after a few hours.

It‚Äôs not a typical makeup base that glides on the skin easily ‚Äî I have to squeeze the tube harder to get the product, then tug at my skin and use my fingers to apply the primer upward. These don‚Äôt bother me at all. In fact, this formula is better than a typical spreadable makeup base, which tends to melt and create residues when I put on foundation or touch up during the day.

üëè Still Going Strong! Experience The Best Selling NYX Fat Oil Lip Drip üíï

NYX is one of my favorite drugstore brands! I love using their Soft Matte Lip Cream and Epic Ink Waterproof Liquid Eyeliner, so I couldn‚Äôt resist trying NYX Fat Oil Lip! üíã I should have bought it years ago, but I was obsessed with K-Beauty lippies, so I only recently decided to give it a try. üòÖ

üíã NYX Fat Oil Lip Drip is still one of their best-selling products, and I can see why. It‚Äôs a dewy, juicy, and hydrating lip gloss that can be used alone or with other lip products. I prefer non-lip-plumping glosses, and Fat Oil Lip Drip fits the bill. It‚Äôs as sticky as other lip oils but not goopy, which I appreciate.

I bought the shades Supermodel (pink) and Newsfeed (red), which beautifully complement my yellowish skin tone. The product also contains üçì Raspberry Oil, üçì Cloudberry Oil, and üùÜ Vegan Squalane, which help retain moisture in my lips.

üßê However, remember that Fat Oil Lip Drip isn‚Äôt a lip tint, so you‚Äôll need to reapply it after eating, and you may want to use lipstick or lip liner for more intense lip colors.

Acne scars can have a lasting impact far beyond the skin‚Äîthey can hold you back from feeling confident, leaving a mark on how you see yourself every day. This patient came to me because her acne scars had taken a toll on her self-esteem for years. She felt like no matter how much she improved other aspects of her appearance, those scars kept her from feeling like her best self. After some research, she decided it was time to take control and begin her journey toward smooth, radiant skin.

This was her second treatment, part of a carefully customized plan I created to target her scars from every angle. Acne scars often require multiple sessions to see dramatic improvement, but with each treatment, I‚Äôm building progress and getting her closer to her ultimate skin goals. For her, I used a combination approach:
‚ú® Bellafill injections to stimulate long-term collagen production and fill in areas of volume loss.
‚ú® TCA cross to target deep, stubborn icepick scars with precision.
‚ú® Halo laser to gently resurface the skin and address tone and texture.
‚ú® CO2 laser for deeper resurfacing, tackling scars at their core and promoting significant collagen remodeling.

Each of these treatments works in synergy to create smoother, more even skin over time. While acne scars don‚Äôt fade overnight, a tailored plan like this ensures I‚Äôm making meaningful, lasting changes with every session.

She‚Äôs already thrilled with the results she‚Äôs seeing, but what excites her most is how this journey has made her feel. She‚Äôs no longer hiding her skin with makeup or avoiding photos‚Äîshe‚Äôs embracing the changes and feeling more like herself again.

I just bought this adorable Beauty of Joseon Glow Charging Rice Duo Set at YesStyle and I love how it cleans and brightens my skin! üåü This duo set includes the BOJ Glow Replenishing Rice Milk, the Ground Rice and Honey Glow Mask, and a cute headband. üß¥üíÜ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

What is BOJ Glow Replenishing Rice Milk?
This rice toner offers rich nutrients to all skin types, creating a smooth and radiant complexion. üåæ‚ú® Formulated with Rice Extract & Rice Amino Acids for antioxidant and moisturizing effects. It features a unique dual-layer formula with a moisture layer and a powder layer to control sebum production, offering extra care to pores.üíß

My Experience:
‚ú® This toner has a lightweight, dual-layer formula and watery texture with sebum powder, so shake it well before using. How to use?

text:
I bought the Refy Summer Color Lip and Cheek Collection in the shade Papaya at Sephora:

Color:
The blush looks more red-orange on me, which is what I was hoping for. The lip gloss and lip blush are more of a neon orange.

Scent:
All of these are fragrance free

Cream Blush:
A stiff, balm formula. I like that it doesn‚Äôt have a dewy finish but I found it very difficult to blend. It looked a little patchy on my cheeks, but I do appreciate that it‚Äôs on the more long-wearing side.

Lip Blush:
A comfortable matte lip balm that blurs the lips. Unfortunately, this smells pretty strongly of pennies and I don‚Äôt like the round bullet shape because my lips are thinner than the shape/size of the bullet. Would‚Äôve liked this more in a proper lipstick shape so I can get a more precise line on my sharp cupid‚Äôs bow.

Tinted Lip Gloss:
Thin, oily, and runny. Given it‚Äôs so bright and pigmented, this gets way too messy. The squeezey tube also contributes to the mess - because it‚Äôs such a thin formula, I accidentally squeeze too much out every time.

Summary:
The Papaya and Guava colors are SO fun and I really like seeing brands launch some near-neon shades. It was a refreshing change of pace! That said, I think these formulas are underwhelming. That said, I am very picky so if you aren‚Äôt as discerning as I am, you may love this collection!

Refy Summer Color Collection is $45 at Sephora: https://rstyle.me/+UmktbcmXrackHxCVW_37Pw

text:
Collagen loss and DEEP scars? Let's talk about the treatment that actually WORKS! 

When it comes to deep, stubborn scars‚Äîespecially stellate pseudoscars‚Äîyou need more than just a basic laser treatment. These scars run deep and wide, making them some of the most challenging to treat. That‚Äôs why I take an aggressive, multi-layered approach to completely transform the skin‚Äîtargeting every layer for real, lasting improvement.

One of the biggest game-changers in this patient‚Äôs treatment? Silicone Microdroplets‚Äîa PERMANENT filler that not only lifts scars but stimulates collagen production for long-term improvement. Unlike other fillers like Bellafill, silicone is more cost-effective while still delivering incredible, lasting results. Over time, it integrates seamlessly into the skin, restoring lost volume and creating a smoother, more even texture.

Here‚Äôs the power-packed combination I used:
‚úîÔ∏è Silicone Microdroplets ‚Äì The ultimate scar-filling and collagen-boosting powerhouse! Unlike temporary fillers, silicone permanently plumps depressed scars, restores volume, and actively improves skin structure over time. 
‚úîÔ∏è Deep FX CO2 Laser ‚Äì Stellate pseudoscars run deep, so a superficial laser wasn‚Äôt enough. This penetrates deep into scar tissue, breaking up tough fibrotic bands and triggering intensive skin regeneration for true resurfacing.
‚úîÔ∏è Active FX CO2 Laser ‚Äì A more controlled, resurfacing pass to refine the skin‚Äôs top layer, improving texture, clarity, and overall smoothness.
‚úîÔ∏è Halo Laser ‚Äì This dual-wavelength laser treats at two levels, addressing both surface irregularities and deep damage to create a smoother, more even complexion.
‚úîÔ∏è Pix E Microneedling RF ‚Äì This radiofrequency-powered microneedlingtightens skin, smooths out irregularities, and boosts collagen from the inside out, making scars less visible over time.

text:
Here‚Äôs the tea üçµ 

You don‚Äôt need to spend a fortune for healthy, glowing skin! ‚ú® I‚Äôve got 5 easy skincare tips using things you already have at home. ‚§µÔ∏è

Facial Steaming with Herbal Tea üßñüèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

Use a bowl of hot water and add a few herbal tea bags like chamomile or green tea. Lean over the bowl with a towel over your head to trap the steam. This helps open up pores, allowing the antioxidants from the tea to nourish your skin, while also relaxing and detoxifying.

Rice Water Toner üçö

Save the water you rinse your rice in (make sure it‚Äôs clean!) and use it as a toner. Rice water is rich in vitamins and minerals that help brighten the skin, reduce dark spots, and tighten pores. Store it in a spray bottle and keep it in the fridge for up to a week.

DIY Honey and Turmeric Spot Treatment üçØ

Mix a tiny amount of turmeric with honey to create a natural spot treatment. Apply it to acne spots or scars and leave it on for 10-15 minutes. The anti-inflammatory properties of turmeric combined with the healing properties of honey can help reduce redness and speed up healing.

Aloe Vera and Cucumber Ice Cubes üßä

Blend aloe vera gel and cucumber juice, pour the mixture into an ice cube tray, and freeze. Rub a cube on your face in the morning to reduce puffiness, soothe irritation, and refresh your skin. The cooling effect also helps to tighten pores.

Overnight Green Tea Mist üåø

Brew a cup of green tea and let it cool completely. Pour it into a spray bottle and keep it in the fridge. Use it as a refreshing facial mist before bed. Green tea is packed with antioxidants, which help repair and rejuvenate the skin overnight.

Gentle reminder that skincare is not a one size fits all so depending on your skin type and your skin needs some of these tips may or may not work for you, but now you have some at home budget friendly options  that are practical and easy! 

If you love the skincare tips I just shared, do me a favour, save this, send it to a friend, and hit that subscribe button. ‚¨ÜÔ∏èüíï

text:
‚ú® ‚ÄúCool‚Äù Solution to Combat Wrinkles - AXIS-Y Vegan Collagen Eye Serum ‚ú®

Thanks to @axisy_official for sending me the Glass Skin Duo - Dark Spot Correcting Glow Serum and Vegan Collagen Eye Serum for review.

Today, I am going to review the üëÄ Vegan Collagen Eye Serum, which is part of the AXIS-Y 6+1+1 series.

‚úÖ Each product from this series is formulated with a combination of 6 nutrient-rich base ingredients, 1 core goal-oriented ingredient, and 1 quality-producing effective technology.

‚ù§Ô∏è What do I think about AXIS-Y Vegan Collagen Eye Serum?

üåø AXIS-Y Vegan Collagen Eye Serum is designed for eye wrinkles, puffiness, and dark circles. I have been using it day and night for about a week, and what I love is its hydrating, soothing, and calming effects. The ingredients in the eye serum are so gentle that I can layer the product with Retinol or other eye creams if I want to.

ü•∞ I love storing the eye cream in the fridge for an ultimate cooling effect that helps to reduce eye puffiness and dark circles. text:
Nature Republic sent me two new shades of my favorite lip product ever - the honey melting lip balms. The two new shades have a glitter finish, which is new for their lineup.

Scent: apricot (one of my favorite scents)
Price: $9.80
Finish: high shine, glossy, smoothing
Texture: thick, cushiony, slightly stiff but then melts on contact, slightly tacky/grippy. (Aka my favorite texture)

I personally prefer the honey melting lips that are opaque and have more base pigment (shades 1‚Äì5.)

Shades 5-10 were also shimmer-free but were more sheer than the first five.

They also launch two plumping/cooling shades in a black and a link, which I haven‚Äôt tried.

Overall I LOVE THESE but the glitter ones are a tad gritty so I don‚Äôt see myself reaching for them.

My suggestions: I would LOVE to see a light peachy pink, a collection of nudes for all skin tones, a cool pink, a hot pink, a bright orangey-red, and a ‚Äúmy lips but better‚Äù plum. Because obviously I need them in every color under the sun. üòÇ

text:
Thrive just launched their EmpowerMattePrecision Lipstick Crayon and they sent me most of the shades! These are $28 and are supposed to be a lip liner and bold matte lipstick in one. 

They describe the formula as a ‚Äúweightless comfort-matte with a velvety-smooth texture that glides on tug-free for even color and a non-sticky finish. Infused with moisturizing ingredients like shea butter, jojoba oil, and sodium hyaluronate, this game-changing matte lipstick nourishes + hydrates lips and remains comfortable to wear all day.‚Äù

My thoughts:
These are probably the most lightweight bold lipstick I‚Äôve tried. They feel ultra-thin and a bit slippery, which might be a good thing depending on your preference. They‚Äôre definitely comfortable, I didn‚Äôt notice my lips feeling particularly dry, but I think there‚Äôs bit too much glide to the formula, they can definitely transfer and get messy. 

Personally, I wouldn‚Äôt feel comfortable wearing such a slippery formula in bold colors, but I also don‚Äôt like lipstick crayons in general because they feel quite young/cheap so this product just isn‚Äôt for me. I shipped these to a lovely follower so she could enjoy them instead! While these don‚Äôt align with my preferences for lipstick, I could see them being someone else‚Äôs favorite if you love ultra-lightweight formulas in a crayon component.

If your preferences usually align with mine, check out Thrive‚Äôs lip liners and lip gloss formulas! They‚Äôre some of my favorite products.

You can purchase the EmpowerMattes at Thrive Causemetics: https://go.shopmy.us/p-5965262

text:
My patient recently came in for a complete skin transformation‚Äîa combination treatment designed to leave her skin looking youthful, radiant, and flawless. She slept peacefully throughout the entire process, allowing me to focus on delivering dramatic yet natural results without any discomfort for her. Here's how I approached her comprehensive treatment:

‚úÖ InstaLift Threads: I started by gently lifting and repositioning sagging skin to create a more refreshed and youthful contour.
‚úÖ @miracucPDOthreads: To further enhance her mid and lower face, I used PDO threads, precisely sculpting and fixing tissue to achieve maximum definition.
‚úÖ Meshfill: For additional firmness and support, I targeted skin laxity with Meshfill, ensuring her results were smooth and sculpted.
‚úÖ BBL HERO Laser: Next, I reduced signs of aging, pigmentation, and age spots across her face, neck, arms, and chest, laying the foundation for a more even skin tone.
‚úÖ Pixel8 RF: Using advanced microneedling and radiofrequency, I evened out her complexion and refined her skin texture.
‚úÖ Halo Hybrid Laser: To address both surface and deeper layers of her skin, I performed a Halo treatment, significantly reducing pores, fine lines, and wrinkles.
‚úÖ CO2 Resurfacing: I finished with my most powerful laser to tighten her skin and erase fine lines, achieving a beautifully smooth and rejuvenated look.

Though she experienced some initial swelling and redness, her recovery was quick and seamless. Now, her skin is glowing, smooth, and incredibly youthful. She‚Äôs overjoyed with her results, and it‚Äôs moments like these that truly highlight the impact of expert care and advanced technology!

text:
Summer Duo for All Skin - Round Lab Birch Moisturizing Cream and SPF 50 üåûüåø

Thanks to @stylevana_sv for sending me this Round Lab Birch Moisturizing Cream (and other goodies) which I longed to try, along with my self-purchased item, Round Lab Birch Juice Moisturizing Sunscreen, which has become a skincare staple in Summer.

ü§ó Use my code INF10KATUSA and shop at @stylevana_sv for 10-15% off! (Links in Profile)

üíô What is Round Lab Birch Moisturizing Cream?

It contains Birch Tree Sap that nourishes the skin by decreasing inflammation, purifying the skin, and hydrating with its extensive minerals, enzymes, proteins, and antioxidants.

Active Ingredients:
* Betula Platyphylla Japonica Juice (10,000ppm): Reduces inflammation, purifies, and hydrates the skin with 17 amino acids, minerals, antioxidants, and vitamins.

* Panthenol: Enhances hydration.

üíô What do I think about Round Lab Birch Moisturizing Cream?

I‚Äôve been using this moisturizer for about a week, and I love it! It‚Äôs not a magical face cream that minimizes pores or brightens the skin in a flash, but it is a good, basic, hydrating moisturizer that calms and nourishes my combo to dry skin. üíß

I like the gel-creamy texture that feels weightless, and the cream sinks into my skin quickly. I can layer sunscreen and makeup afterward without creating rubbery residues or feeling heavy.

The formulation is mild, and the cream is unscented. It calms my hormonal acne, and my sebum production is under control.

This cream is designed for all skin types, even sensitive skin. However, if you have very dry skin, an essence or an ampoule is recommended for better moisturizing.

I apply Round Lab Birch Juice Moisturizing Sunscreen after the moisturizer, and the sunscreen glides on the skin effortlessly. The lotion texture of the Round Lab sunscreen is so light and runny. It has become my go-to sunscreen in high-humidity weather! Great for oily to combo skin. üåû

üíô What is Round Lab Birch Moisturizing Sunscreen SPF 50+ PA++++?

- SPF 50+/PA++++
- Combines Birch Tree Sap which nourishes skin by decreasing inflammation
- Contains amino acids, minerals, and Birch Sap vitamins to protect the skin from drying and prevent loss of hydration.
- A hydrating sunscreen that does double duty as a moisturizer, for all skin types, especially oily and combination skin.

üíô What do I think about Round Lab Birch Moisturizing Sunscreen SPF 50+ PA++++? 

It is perfect for combo and oily skin. The texture is a milky lotion that goes smooth on my skin, even in areas with large pores, without feeling sticky or tuning my skin when I apply it. It isn't an oil-control sunscreen, but I do love using it as it balances my skin moisture. No white cast and is perfect to use as a makeup base. üíï

What is your favorite moisturizer or sunscreen? Have you tried any products from Round Lab? Share your thoughts below! üòä

text:
I purchased the new Gxve Beauty dewy plump collagen lip gel in bouquet the Sephora sale! Here‚Äôs my quick review:

This is not a lip gel like I was expecting. When I hear ‚Äúgel‚Äù I think Fitglow lip serums, make beauty lip serum, live tinted huegloss, etc - a cushiony, buttery smooth formula with some slip.

The Gxve Beauty dewy plump lip gel is not that at all. To me, it feels exactly like their bubble pop electric gold in different packaging, but with a smoothing quality.

It‚Äôs a VERY thick, quite sticky formula with a strong cake batter smell and an insanely impressive smoothing quality. So avoid these if you want a lightweight formula, but pick one up if you love thicker glosses that smooth lip lines.

The shade bouquet is really pretty but it‚Äôs not even close to what the pictures looked like on Sephora. I thought I was getting a bright pinky coral shade, but bouquet is a light milky pink. I think one of the darker shades would suit me best because bouquet leaves a bit of a white ring around my lips.

Overall, I don‚Äôt think the product fits the name but it‚Äôs fantastic if you like a thick, smoothing gloss.

Link to product at Sephora: https://rstyle.me/+iNWP8bYuAojLHdklv4Q3-Q

text:
üåä Say Hello to Hydration! üåø Meet The Plant Base Waterfall Moist Balanced Hyaluronic Acid Ampoule!

üíß A big thanks to @theplantbase_official The Plant Base for sending me this Hyaluronic Acid Ampoule for review ‚Äî it couldn‚Äôt have come at a better time as I‚Äôm dealing with some acne issues.

What is it? ü§î
This ampoule contains just one ingredient‚Äî100% Sodium Hyaluronate! üåü It has smaller molecules than Hyaluronic Acid, allowing it to penetrate the skin‚Äôs top layer (the epidermis) and reach deeper layers for enhanced hydration. Meanwhile, Hyaluronic Acid‚Äôs larger molecules coat the skin and prevent water loss. üí¶

Because ‚ÄúHyaluronic Acid‚Äù is a more recognizable term, some companies (including The Plant Base) label products as containing Hyaluronic Acid when they actually contain Sodium Hyaluronate. üß¥

You can use this ampoule on its own after cleansing and toning, or layer it with other products. It delivers multiple skincare benefits‚Äîhydrating, revitalizing, and moisturizing. Plus, it‚Äôs vegan and free from artificial fragrances. üå±

ü•∞ My Experience:
I‚Äôve been dealing with some acne lately, so I‚Äôve been using Benzoyl Peroxide to target the affected areas. That means I need a hydrating essence to prevent the dryness and irritation that can come with it. This ampoule has been the perfect solution ‚Äî it softens and calms my skin without being too thick or too lightweight. It absorbs easily, glides on effortlessly, and pairs beautifully with other The Plant Base products (I‚Äôm currently using their Cica Gel and Cica Cream for blemish treatment). üåø

During the daytime, I skip moisturizer and just use this ampoule with sunscreen for protection. üåû It‚Äôs a simple yet effective routine that works great for my combination skin, especially in humid weather.

And did I mention the packaging? üéÅ It‚Äôs part of The Plant Base‚Äôs Green Package campaign, reducing plastic use by 60% with paper tubes! üåç‚ôªÔ∏è

What‚Äôs your favorite hyaluronic acid? Share your thoughts below! üëáüí¨

Want to know the secret to looking youthful and sculpted without anyone knowing you‚Äôve had work done?

My patient visits me annually for my signature heart-shaped facial sculpting look- trusting only my expertise to keep her looking youthful, balanced, and sculpted. With these regular maintenance treatments, she continues to defy aging and maintain her timeless look. This time, she wanted to fine-tune key areas for a refreshed and defined appearance. 

Starting with her temples, I filled in hollowness to support her brows and create a more harmonious contour. Next, I enhanced her cheeks for a structured, sculpted look and added filler to her jawline to sharpen and define her natural 90¬∞ angle. And guess what guys? The chin is in! I added some subtle but much needed projection to complete the heart-shaped symmetry she desired.I used filler to address her brows, for added bone definition and lift, enhancing her overall facial balance. Finally, her lips‚Äîalready gorgeous‚Äîwere given a subtle plump for a soft, natural enhancement and a keyhole pout. 

The result is a stunning, refreshed appearance with precise sculpting that highlights her natural beauty while achieving her goals. This is exactly why she chose me. Other providers who are not as experienced cannot deliver these results and often leave their patients with that overdone look. It‚Äôs all about knowledge, meticulous planning, and technique. Each patient‚Äôs facial features vary so it is extremely important to go to a professional that takes the time to asses your features.

text:
Very casual cheek swatches of the new Rare Beauty soft pinch luminous blushes.

Pls ignore my red nose, allergies have been kicking my ass.

These are $26 each and the brand claims that they‚Äôre a hybrid between a powder blush and their silky touch highlighter.

My experience is that these are way too shimmery to be a blush, and way too pigmented to be a highlighter. They emphasize texture due to the metallic nature of the formula, so I‚Äôd recommend this to people who either have extremely smooth skin, or don‚Äôt mind the texture-emphasizing effect.

I also found the deepest shades extremely difficult to blend despite only applying a tiny bit, tapping off excess, and blending some on the back of my hand. It‚Äôs just not a formula I find flattering in any way.

I do have friends with great skin who tried this and the product looked really good on them, but on my acne prone skin‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs a pass for me.

The last cheek swatch I showed was the blush in cheer layered over their liquid blush in hope, and that‚Äôs the most flattering way to wear it IMO - as a blush topper. I don‚Äôt personally see the value in purchasing a product solely to be a blush topper but we‚Äôre all different!

What do you think? Would you like these?

The shades are pretty nice. I'd say they are flexible considering 2 or 3 could work for me depending on the undertones and what I use on top of it. It lasts on my throughout the day without breaking down or getting too greasy. But if is definitely a radiant finish. If you want matte, you can mattify it with a powder on top. I was able to comfortably apply a good amount of this to get the full protection, but I personally still would use my regular sunscreen and use a thinner layer of this on top as a skin tint, not my standalone sunscreen. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

text:
Recover Forehead lines and Wrinkles

"Say goodbye to forehead lines and wrinkles with these top skincare tips! ‚ú® Consistency is key, so remember to hydrate, use sunscreen, and incorporate a retinoid into your routine. Botox or fillers can also work wonders. Embrace a smoother, youthful complexion!"

1.  Hydrate Regularly:  Keeping your skin moisturized helps plump the skin and reduce the appearance of lines.  
   Hashtags: #Hydration #Moisturize #HealthySkin #PlumpSkin #SkinCareEssentials #WrinklePrevention

2.  Use Sunscreen Daily: UV rays accelerate skin aging, so apply sunscreen every day to prevent further damage.  
   Hashtags: #Sunscreen #SPFProtection #SunDamage #AntiAging #UVProtection #YouthfulSkin

3.  Incorporate Retinoids:  Retinoids boost collagen production, reducing fine lines over time.  
   Hashtags: #Retinoids #CollagenBoost #AntiAgingSkincare #SmoothSkin #SkinRenewal #WrinkleFighter

4.  Try Botox:  Botox relaxes the muscles responsible for forehead lines, smoothing the skin temporarily.  
   Hashtags: #Botox #WrinkleTreatment #SmoothForehead #YouthfulAppearance #CosmeticTreatment #AgingGracefully

5.  Use Hyaluronic Acid:  This ingredient helps retain skin moisture, making wrinkles less visible.  
   Hashtags: #HyaluronicAcid #HydratedSkin #MoistureLock #PlumpSkin #AntiWrinkle #GlowingSkin

6.  Apply Vitamin C: A potent antioxidant that brightens skin and boosts collagen, reducing fine lines.  
   Hashtags: #VitaminC #Antioxidants #BrighteningSkin #CollagenBoost #AntiAgingSkincare #RadiantSkin

7. Avoid Over-Exfoliation:  Over-exfoliating can thin the skin, making wrinkles more pronounced.  
   Hashtags: #GentleExfoliation #SkinCareBalance #HealthySkin #SkinCareRoutine #ExfoliationTips #WrinklePrevention

8. Stay Hydrated:  Drinking plenty of water keeps skin supple and reduces wrinkle depth.  
   Hashtags: #StayHydrated #WaterForSkin #HealthyLifestyle #SkinHydration #YouthfulGlow #AntiAging

9. Facial Exercises:    Strengthening facial muscles can help reduce the appearance of lines.  
   Hashtags: #FacialExercises #FaceYoga #NaturalBeauty #SkinFirming #AntiWrinkle #HealthySkin

10. Get Enough Sleep:  Quality sleep allows your skin to repair itself, reducing the formation of new wrinkles.  
   Hashtags: #BeautySleep #RestfulNights #SkinRepair #SleepAndSkin #HealthyHabits #YouthfulSkin

11. Healthy Diet:
 Consuming antioxidants and omega-3 fatty acids helps maintain skin elasticity.  
   Hashtags: #HealthyDiet #SkinElasticity #Omega3 #Antioxidants #NutritionForSkin #GlowingSkin

12. Avoid Repetitive Facial Movements: Repeated expressions like frowning can deepen lines over time.  
   Hashtags: #RelaxYourFace #ExpressionLines #WrinklePrevention #SkinCareTips #AntiAging #YouthfulAppearance

üòÖ I feel like I‚Äôve been influenced! Tower 28 BeachPlease Cream Blush ‚ò∫Ô∏è

üí∏ After browsing countless makeup reels, I purchased the Tower 28 BeachPlease Cream Blush from Sephora. Initially, I had my eyes set on the Rare Beauty Soft Pinch Luminous Powder Blush. However, upon seeing it in person, I hesitated because of its highly pigmented colors and the potential to enhance my already large pores with its luminous effect. ‚ú®

ü§© Surprisingly, I stumbled upon the Tower 28 BeautyPlease Cream Blush in a hidden area, not prominently displayed on the shelf. It was üíï love at first sight! I was drawn to its creamy texture, intense yet not overly pigmented colors, and its sleek and simple packaging. The transparent cover made it easy for me to choose the shade. üôå

üéÄ I must admit, I‚Äôm head over heels in love with this cream blush. I picked up the shades üòçHappy Hour, a sun-kissed coral pink, and üí≠ Dream Hour, a bright pink, for my daily look. Both shades are perfect for spring and summer, and I love their buildability. I apply them with my fingers, tapping the color onto my cheekbones. The best part is that there‚Äôs ‚ùå no glitter or ‚ùå shimmer, so it doesn‚Äôt accentuate my pores.

I‚Äôve also applied it to my lips, and the cream blush gives a velvet, blurry finish. üëÑ It‚Äôs cute, but I prefer a shiny effect, so I top it off with a clear lip gloss.

üí° Tips:

Try using this blush on a cream or liquid surface for seamless application. I apply it on top of a liquid foundation and gently press it with loose powder. You can also use it on the eye area or lips as cream eyeshadows or lipstick.

text:
~PR~
Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this mineral sunscreen from Minu today! 
üîÜ
- UV Filters: Zinc Oxide and Titanium Dioxide
- It has a gel cream lotion texture
- Leaves a white cast on my skin tone
- Does not work well in my facial hair
- Has a natural finish
- Does not sting me eyes
- Around 12 pumps to get the necessary amount for proper protection (around 1/2 teaspoon for face/neck)
- No added fragrance or essential oils
- Water resistant
- Around $58 for 50mL. Can be purchased from their website or credo beauty.
üîÜ
This tint is definitely darker than I expected, but this is still a mineral sunscreen at the end of the day. I do like that it blends in evenly and it doesn‚Äôt leave streaks on my face. It is water resistant and feels lightweight on the skin. Says that ‚Äúonce blended into skin, the tint will vanish and the light reflecting pigments will produce a luminous brightening effect.‚Äù That does not seem to be the case on my skin tone because there definitely is a visible white cast left on me. I don‚Äôt really like that ‚Äúuniversal‚Äù tint claim when it leaves a white cast on deeper skin. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

Green Dragon¬†- Sage and peppermint¬†

Orange Crush¬†- Citrus scent
Pink Magic¬†- Watermelon

* my favorites

text:
Alright, guys, let's talk FACIAL SCULPTING. This patient to me with a clear goal: to achieve a sharper, more masculine, and ultra-contoured look that is super in demand right now. He wanted definition, structure, and balance‚Äîa face that commands attention. And when it comes to achieving that kind of transformation, pairing filler with threads is how I can achieve the ultimate results.

For this patient, I strategically placed filler in his chin, cheeks, temples, and jawline to build volume where he needed it most, creating bold, defined angles while maintaining a natural look. The filler was all about structure‚Äîbuilding out the strong, masculine features he wanted. But sculpting the face isn‚Äôt just about adding volume; it‚Äôs also about lifting and refining. That‚Äôs where the threads came in.

By placing threads in his midface and jawline, I was able to lift and tighten the skin, enhancing his natural bone structure and giving him that sleek, chiseled look. The combination of filler and threads isn‚Äôt just powerful; it‚Äôs precise. Together, they work to create harmony and proportion while boosting collagen for long-lasting results.

What I love about this case is how it highlights the artistry of male facial sculpting. It‚Äôs not about overdoing it‚Äîit‚Äôs about accentuating the natural anatomy of the face, bringing balance and symmetry while maintaining a look that‚Äôs undeniably masculine. Many providers end up leaving their patients looking overdone, but not me. I know exactly how to achieve that subtle, yet effective look so my patients look great without anyone being able to guess they had anything done.

Dr. Jason Emer is a board-certified dermatologist, specializing in cosmetic, laser and procedural dermatology, including facial sculpting with fillers and hi definition body contouring transformations in West Hollywood, California. Dr. Emer is behind some of Hollywood's most defined bodies, impeccable skin, and chiseled facial features. He is an aesthetic visionary who dares to be different.

Really like the packaging, so much more sanitary than normal cushions tbh

Green cushion (23W)
- Very natural finish (my mum couldn‚Äôt tell I was wearing foundation)
- Better if you want higher coverage
- Thicker formula and clung to my dry patches (maybe better for oily skin)
- Didn‚Äôt settle into pores
- Could get a little cakey towards the end of the day, so make sure to blend and set well
- Lower SPF than the pink cushion üò¢

Pink Cushion (23W)
- prefer this one a lot more
- glowy/hydrating cushion, so this was really good for my dry skin
- Didn‚Äôt settle into pores
- Felt more blendable than the green one
- Thinner formula which I prefer
- Only 3 shades (1 less than the green one)
- SP50++ üôå
- lighter coverage
- Still looked good as new after 5 hrs???

Products were gifted but these are my own opinions and experiences

‚ú® The Most Underrated Brightening Toner Pad from Korea - Numbuzin No.3 Radiance Glowing Jumbo Essence Pad ‚ú® 

‚ú®YesStyle Reward Code: BEAUTYKAT321 ‚ú®

I always wanted to try K-Beauty Toner Pad and after doing some research, I chose 
Numbuzin No.3 Radiance Glowing Jumbo Essence Pad even though I seldom see people talking about it. ‚ù§Ô∏è What caught my eye are the product ingredients which contain 50 types of ferment extracts ü§© for skin revitalization, and they use üåø biodegradable and unbleached vegan cotton ‚òÅÔ∏è for cotton pads which I was impressed with. 

After 3 weeks of usage, I totally fell for this product ‚ù§Ô∏è - my skin is brighter and smoother, and the blackheads on my t-zone area seem less visible. ü•∞

Having said that, this product is not a purely hydrating essence pad but a brightening, gentle-peeling product that also contains fruit extracts for 

1Ô∏è‚É£ Removing skin impurities and dead skin cells,
2Ô∏è‚É£ Refining skin texture and large pores, and 
3Ô∏è‚É£ Promoting clear and transparent skin complexion 

So AVOID EYE AREAS as instructed ‚ö†Ô∏è 

Since I have normal to dry skin and I try this product in Winter, I will use this essence pad to wipe my face only in the evening which helps me to remove the last trace of makeup and impurities without drying my skin. 

I will also use it as a facial mask but only 2-3 times a week and leave the mask on my skin for 3 minutes. I learned my lesson as I left the mask on the skin for almost 10 minutes while recording this reel. My skin became tight and tingling when I removed the mask. I am not allergic to the product but I think the fruit extracts or other fermented ingredients are doing their jobs by removing excess sebum so if you leave the mask on the skin for too long, it becomes too much for the skin.

üëç It took me some time to adjust the product's usage but once I developed my routine, I could see the brightening result and I am happy about it.

text:
How refreshed does he look?! My patient has been absolutely crushing his fitness goals, but his face was telling a different story. Volume loss made him look tired and older than he felt. Gaunt cheeks and tired eyes weren't the look he was going for! He needed a refresh, a boost‚Äîand he knew exactly who to call: me! üòâüìû

So, how do we achieve this "undetectable" look? It's all about precision, artistry, and a deep understanding of facial anatomy and proportions. It's not just about filling lines; it's about restoring lost volume in strategic areas to rebuild the natural scaffolding of the face. Here‚Äôs the approach I took with this patient:

‚úîÔ∏è Mid-face and Cheekbones: The mid-face is crucial for a youthful appearance. As we age, we lose volume in this area, leading to flattened cheeks and a less defined contour. The key is to avoid overfilling, which can create an unnatural, "puffy" look. Instead, I focus on creating subtle definition and lifting the cheeks to restore a more youthful and defined contour. Boom.

‚úîÔ∏è Under-eye Area: Say goodbye to tired eyes. I banished shadows and smoothed things out, instantly revitalizing his entire look. My goal is to create a smooth, seamless transition between the lower eyelid and the cheek, creating a refreshed and rested appearance without looking "done." This is where the art of undetectable aesthetics truly shines ‚Äì the results are so natural that people will simply think you look well-rested and vibrant. Instant win!

Fast forward a few days, and the transformation is undeniable. He looks younger, healthier, and radiates confidence. His friends are blown away and they see a new level of energy and confidence! That's the Dr. Emer difference: game-changing results that speak for themselves.

The winning formula:
‚úÖ Sharper features, a stronger jawline, and defined cheekbones.
‚úÖ Bright, energized eyes that demand attention.
‚úÖ A naturally powerful, confident look.

This is about empowering my patients to look and feel their best by enhancing their natural beauty in a way that looks completely effortless! 

Ready for some sculpting? üíâ

Dr. Jason Emer is a board-certified dermatologist, specializing in cosmetic, laser and procedural dermatology, including facial sculpting with fillers and hi definition body contouring transformations in West Hollywood, California. Dr. Emer is behind some of Hollywood's most defined bodies, impeccable skin, and chiseled facial features. He is an aesthetic visionary who dares to be different.

It is a fun product to use as I can use it 2-3 times a week or whenever I feel like having an extra hydration for my skin. I love storing it in the fridge for a cool, refreshing and tightening effect.

text:
üíï The Most Popular Makeup Item at Sephora - Rare Beauty Soft Pinch Liquid Blush

I‚Äôve always wanted to try Rare Beauty Soft Pinch Liquid Blush, and I finally got my hands on Hope (Nude Mauve - Beige Pink) and a mini size of Virtue (Beige Peach). I love this product‚Äôs pigmentation and weightless texture, which blends and builds beautifully for a soft, lightly dewy, and healthy look. üå∏‚ú®

I used only my fingers to blend the blush on top of my liquid foundation. It didn‚Äôt ruin my foundation or leave a rubbery residue on my face. But I was surprised by how pigmented the liquid blush was, especially in the shade Hope. Luckily, it was easy to correct the amount I applied. I simply used my clean hands to press my face lightly so some of the color transferred back to my hands, then used a tissue to clean it up. üôå

My advice: just place 1-2 dots on the back of your hand and apply a small amount to your face. It‚Äôs buildable, so you can add more as needed. I also use a loose powder to set the blush, so it lasts all day long. üïíüåº

By the way, these blushes are made in Korea. Do you know any dupes for Rare Beauty from K-Beauty? Will you choose Hope or Virtue? Share your thoughts below! üí≠üíñ

This young patient walked into my office very depressed, her confidence shattered. She should‚Äôve been out laughing with her friends, posting selfies, living her best life. Instead? When they came to me, they knew one thing: I don‚Äôt follow the same rules as everyone else. Why? Because the old rules don‚Äôt get LIFE CHANGING results!

I built her plan like I build all my treatments: customized, aggressive, and results-driven.

üíé Emer Skin Protocol‚ÄîThis is the secret sauce and they KEY to healing properly. My exclusive skincare regimen ensures her skin heals better, faster, and stronger than ever. No shortcuts. No skipping steps.

I didn‚Äôt pass this off to an aesthetician... I personally handled her treatments! Why? Because I knew what was at stake. For her, this wasn‚Äôt just about clearing acne‚Äîit was about regaining her life, her confidence, her happiness. 

Fast forward a couple of months, and her results are INSANE. The acne? Gone. The scars? Faded. Her pores? Practically invisible. She‚Äôs glowing like never before‚Äîinside and out! ü§©

text:
‚ÄúMy skin is so dehydrated and I‚Äôve tried everything üò≠‚Äù
But did you try üëá

1Ô∏è‚É£ a Hydrating Toner? - This helps replenish the water deep in your thirsty skin!

2Ô∏è‚É£ What about Slugging? - This helps to create a temporary barrier on your skin that holds the water in your skin, slowing down dehydration.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Do you use Ceramides? - These all important lipids help to stregthen your skin barrier (which is the reason your skin feels dehydrated, the skin barrier isn't working the way it's supposed to) get to the root cause of your dehydration by giving your skin barrier some love!

4Ô∏è‚É£ Maybe Facial Oil? - This might help in a few mays. Facial oil is not occlusive (popular myth) but it might help add a little more moisture that can resist the water escaping your skin. Certain oils have favorable fatty acid profiles that can help with a healthy skin barrier function (evening primrose, chia seed, sea buckthorn, rosehip).

5Ô∏è‚É£ How About Sleeping with Humidifier? -  A dry environment encourages trans epidermal water loss (TEWL) resulting in dehydrated skin. Try sleeping with a humidifier on to keep your space and skin hydrated.

text:
Best practices for healing your barrierüëá

üëâ avoid using any harsh exfoliants while healing (retinol, aha, bha, vitamin c, azelaic acid, benzoyl peroxide etc)

üëâ add soothing hydration to address dehydration symptoms

üëâavoid drying forms of alcohol, fragrance and essential oils as they can be irritating when your skin barrier is vulnerable

üëâuse a nourishing moisturizer or slug to help mimic the protective benefits of your skin barrier (because the one you got is out of commission right now)

üëâ be patient, healing can take time, allow at least 2-6 weeks (sometimes longer!)

‚ö†Ô∏èBUT! all of this is just soothing the SYMPTOMS of your damaged skin barrier (and those symptoms can be painful). You need to get to the source to heal your skin barrier and nothing does it better than ceramides, cholesterol, and fatty acids!

üî¨Why? Because your skin barrier is actually composed of these all important lipids (50% ceramides, 25% cholesterol, 25% fatty acids).

üëâSo if your skin barrier is weak or damaged, make sure to give it some lipid love!‚ù§Ô∏è

text:
Products I really want to love but I don‚Äôt - Part II

1Ô∏è‚É£ Shiseido Integrate Flat Skin Maker UV SPF50 - This product is a multi-functional face moisturizer that is supposed to be used as a lotion, sunscreen, and makeup base for large pores. I always loved using Shiseido Integrate as the quality of this brand is impressive. üëç Unfortunately, this product irritates my eyes badly and my tears keep rolling after using it. ü•∫

2Ô∏è‚É£ SK-II Facial Treatment Essence - I used to sell it and it was our best-selling item at all times. My customers swear that it improves their skin texture and complexion but to be honest with you, it doesn‚Äôt do much on my skin and I don‚Äôt see a huge difference after using it for some time. üí∞ With this price tag, I would rather choose SK-II Clear Lotion, Facial Treatment Mask, SKINPOWER Advanced Cream, or Eye Cream. ü•∞

3Ô∏è‚É£ Sofina Primavista Day Treatment Balm Foundation Roller Type - this is a balm-like foundation with long-lasting moisturizing benefits. I love how it promotes light hydration but it takes time to roll and apply the foundation to my face. I have to admit that I pressed the roller too hard and the edge of it grasped the product randomly so the foundation looks bad after only 2 or 3 times of usage. On top of that, it attracts dirt and fiber easily. Such a bummer üòï!

4Ô∏è‚É£ Beauty of Joseon Matte Sun Stick - I love BOJ but this sun stick is a huge disappointment. üò£ It doesn‚Äôt glide on my skin and it creates rubbery residues. üò¢

5Ô∏è‚É£ Rare Beauty Positive Light Under Eye Brightener - after reading so many positive reviews on this product, I decided to give it a try and I don‚Äôt get it! ü§Ø It‚Äôs too light to cover dark eye circles, and it is too difficult to use with its metal applicator. For example, you have to use a fingertip to blend the product after applying it with the metal tip; and if you want to cool your under-eye areas solely by using the metal applicator, you have to blend the product later. In this case, I would rather have separate products for different purposes üôà

Have you tried these products? And what products disappoint you? Share your thoughts below. ‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è

text:
Tried Fenty hair wash products on my 4c hair üíÜüèæ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èü´ßI‚Äôm not mad at it.

Detailed review below: 

The whole line is scented but to me the smell is not overbearing at all which is a plus.

The rich one shampoo: 8/10~ it‚Äôs a great cleanser my hair and scalp felt clean on the first round,  It foams a lot and quickly. Now I do wish it had more moisture because when I rinsed my hair the second time it did feel a little bit dry and I would not be able to detangle my hair.

The rich one conditioner: 9.5/10~ now this was very moisturizing as soon as it hit my hair, I could feel the softness in the slip in my hair was amazing. I could‚Äôve detangled my whole head easily with it.

The richer one deep conditioner: 7/10~ for a deep conditioner the slip wasn‚Äôt amazing The consistency was lighter than the conditioner. Probably why my hair didn‚Äôt really love it like that. But for looser hair texture it might be great. 
However i will try it again without the conditioner and leave it on to see if it makes a difference.

‚ú® Introducing the Medicube RF Ultra Tune 40.68 ‚Äì your new at-home skincare game changer! ‚ú®

Gifted by Medicube

This high-tech, 2-in-1 tool uses Dual Tune-Wave‚Ñ¢ technology to work magic on skin elasticity and fine lines, leaving your skin smooth and supple. üôå‚ú®

üíÜ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Home Spa Vibes: No need for special gels; simply use it after your skincare product is fully absorbed. However, I use it with Aloe Vera Gel, Medicube Collagen Jelly Cream, and Medicube PDRN Pink Peptide Serum. All of these work perfectly with the device ‚Äì I feel more heat if I wait for the product to absorb, so I prefer using the device with Aloe Vera Gel or Medicube Collagen Jelly Cream. üå∏ It glides on the skin better with the gel and I feel more relaxed while using the RF Ultra Tune.

üîã Powerful Yet Gentle: Combining RF (radio frequency) and MC (microcurrent) tech, it boosts skin elasticity and contours, leaving your skin looking firmer and more youthful. üíñ

üì± Maximize Results with the AGE-R App: Track your progress, get personalized tips, and optimize your routine with custom settings! üåü

‚ú® How RF and MC work in skincare:

RF (Radio Frequency) uses electromagnetic waves to heat the deeper layers of the skin, stimulating collagen and elastin production. This helps to improve skin elasticity, reduce fine lines, and promote a firmer, youthful appearance. The gentle heat also encourages blood circulation, making your skin look more radiant and toned. ‚ú®

MC (Microcurrent) uses low-level electrical currents to stimulate facial muscles. This helps tone and lift the skin, improve contours, and reduce sagging. It also supports the absorption of skincare products, boosting overall skin health and vitality. üíñ

Some of you may know that Medicube has different beauty devices, so how is the Medicube RF Ultra Tune 40.68 different from their similar devices ‚Äì the Deep Shot and Age-R Booster Pro (6-in-1 device)?

‚ú® How is it different from the Deep Shot?
The key difference is that the Ultra Tune operates at a frequency approximately 20 times higher than the Deep Shot, providing more powerful RF elasticity care without the need for a separate gel! üí´ Plus, while the Deep Shot combines RF and ultrasound waves and is recommended for use 2-3 times a week, the Ultra Tune uses RF + MC technology, making it perfect for daily use. üëè

‚ú® How is it different from the Age-R Booster Pro (6-in-1 device)?
The Age-R Booster Pro combines Electroporation, Microcurrent, EMS, and Electric Needles for different skin care purposes, focusing on vibration for muscle training, skin firmness, pore care, anti-aging, and glowing results. Meanwhile, the RF Ultra Tune 40.68 is designed to give you a luxurious at-home experience, focusing on RF technology that targets skin elasticity, fine lines, and pore care. ‚ú®

üí´ My Experience: After using it for 2 weeks, I‚Äôve noticed smoother skin, refined pores, and even some subtle improvement in my laugh lines! üòç I love how gentle it feels, with no muscle twitching like other devices. I‚Äôm definitely seeing potential for long-term results! üí™‚ú®

If you have a flat lip line like me and don‚Äôt have time for detailed lip contouring, here‚Äôs a quick tip to achieve fuller lips with natural results:

First, apply a glossy lip gloss to fill in your lips. 

Then, use a lip liner with a rounded tip in a shade similar to your lip gloss to define your natural lip line. Start by drawing the lower middle part, followed by the upper middle part‚Äîdon‚Äôt worry about being perfect! I like to create a rounded, smooth shape and slightly extend the line outside my natural lip line for a more natural, feminine look.

Next, extend the lip liner towards the sides of your lips. Avoid making sharp points at the corners‚Äîrounding them off will give you a softer, younger appearance.

text:
~PR~
Happy SUNday! I am reviewing this mineral sunscreen from Everyday Humans today! 
üîÜ
- UV Filters: Zinc Oxide
- It has a light cream texture
- Leaves a white cast on my skin tone
- Does not work well in my facial hair
- Has a natural matte finish, dry touch velvety feel
- Does not sting my eyes
- No added fragrance or essential oils
- It does have that butyloctyl salicylate that acts kinda like a chemical UV filter but sometimes put in ‚Äú100% mineral sunscreens‚Äù
- Around $22 for 50mL. Can be purchased from their website or retailers like Target.
üîÜ
Now this one is a mineral sunscreen so my hopes were not high however, I did love their sunscreen serum. That was one of my contenders for favorite sunscreen of the year last year, so I was open to the possibilities. I do appreciate the velvety dry touch feel of this sunscreen though. This may be a good mineral sunscreen for oily skin if you have a lighter skin tone and don't have coarse dark facial hair like I do. Let me know in a comment if you have any other questions!

text:
I used the Erewhon x Sofia Richie Grainge Sweet Cherry Smoothie as loose inspiration for my at-home version using only ingredients I already had on hand! I wanted this to be a meal so I added Greek yogurt and protein powder but you don‚Äôt have to do that. I do eat quite a healthful diet so this was cost effective for me, but it depends what kind of ingredients you keep in your kitchen.

I eye-balled everything and this made a little over two servings!

I chose to omit the colostrum, dragon fruit powder, and magnesium powder, and I‚Äôm sure that‚Äôs one of the reasons the price is so high at Erewhon. (I take a magnesium supplement already and I don‚Äôt see the need for colostrum or dragon fruit powder. TBH colostrum makes me feel a little ethically wrong but curious to hear your thoughts.)

I didn‚Äôt like that the Erewhon smoothie was basically all fruit and little substance, so I highly recommend adding protein like I did!

My version:
Frozen mixed berries
Frozen dark cherries
Frozen pineapple
Tart cherry juice
Coconut cream
Almond milk
Greek yogurt
Vanilla protein powder
Maple syrup

Erewhon‚Äôs ingredients:
Dark cherries
Pineapple
Avocado
Tart cherry juice
Almond milk
Coconut cream
Colostrum
Magnesium powder
Maple syrup
Dragon fruit powder

Smoothies are so easy because you don‚Äôt have to measure anything and you can just throw in whatever you feel like that day, and it‚Äôs a great way to get more fruits and veggies into your diet.

Let me know if you want more smoothie ideas, I know it‚Äôs not my usual content but I really enjoy sharing my recipes.

text:
Beauty Hacks 
Korean Glass Skin: The Ultimate Skincare Trend 

Korean beauty (K-beauty) has taken the global beauty industry by storm, and one of its most iconic trends is the concept of "glass skin." Glass skin refers to a complexion that is incredibly smooth, luminous, and translucent, much like a piece of glass. Achieving this flawless, dewy look is the result of meticulous skincare routines designed to nourish, hydrate, and perfect the skin over time.

At the heart of glass skin is the idea of healthy, well-hydrated skin. It‚Äôs not just about masking imperfections or covering up with makeup. Instead, glass skin emphasizes the importance of achieving beauty from within, using a combination of skincare products and techniques that focus on long-term results. The goal is a clear, even-toned complexion that reflects light effortlessly, giving the face a radiant, almost ethereal glow.

     The Key Components of a Glass Skin Routine

Achieving glass skin involves a comprehensive skincare regimen, with a focus on hydration, exfoliation, and protection. Here are some key steps:

1. Double Cleansing: The first step in the glass skin routine is the K-beauty staple of double cleansing. This process involves using an oil-based cleanser to remove makeup, sunscreen, and impurities, followed by a water-based cleanser to thoroughly clean the skin. Proper cleansing is crucial for preventing breakouts and ensuring that the skin is prepared to absorb subsequent skincare products.

2.      Exfoliation: Regular exfoliation helps remove dead skin cells, promoting smoother and brighter skin. Gentle exfoliants like AHAs, BHAs, or enzymes work to unclog pores and refine skin texture without causing irritation, which is important for maintaining the smooth, clear base necessary for glass skin.

3. Toning : Korean toners are designed to hydrate and balance the skin‚Äôs pH, as well as prepare it to absorb serums and moisturizers. Hydrating toners, often infused with ingredients like hyaluronic acid or rose water, deliver essential moisture to the skin, making it appear plump and fresh.

4. Essences and Serums : Essences are lightweight, hydrating liquids that help boost the skin‚Äôs moisture levels. Serums, on the other hand, are more concentrated and are used to target specific skin concerns such as hyperpigmentation, fine lines, or dullness. Layering these products is key to achieving the deep hydration that gives glass skin its signature reflective quality.

5.  Moisturizing. : A rich, hydrating moisturizer seals in all the previous layers of hydration. Look for moisturizers with humectants like glycerin and hyaluronic acid, which draw moisture into the skin, as well as emollients like ceramides and fatty acids to strengthen the skin barrier and lock in moisture.

6. Sunscreen. : The final step, and perhaps the most important, is applying sunscreen. UV protection is critical to prevent sun damage, which can lead to premature aging and dull skin. Korean sunscreens are often lightweight and formulated to leave the skin looking dewy, adding to the overall glow.

      Why Is Glass Skin So Popular?

The appeal of glass skin lies in its emphasis on natural beauty. Unlike makeup-heavy trends, it focuses on achieving a healthy, radiant complexion that doesn‚Äôt rely on cosmetics for coverage. Instead, it encourages a holistic approach to skincare that prioritizes hydration, nourishment, and protection. Moreover, the glow achieved with glass skin makes the face appear youthful, fresh, and vibrant ‚Äî qualities that are universally desired.

Ultimately, glass skin is more than just a trend; it‚Äôs a lifestyle that promotes skincare as a form of self-care, teaching individuals to appreciate the beauty of healthy, well-maintained skin.#love

text:
Thrive Causemetics sent me their new sheer strength lip plumping peptide lip glosses!

Description: ‚ÄúOur peptide-powered, ultra-hydrating gloss instantly plumps and revives lips with a hint of tint and all-day moisture for visibly fuller, smoother-looking lips.‚Äù

Formula: not thick or cushiony but noticeably grippy (or sticky if you prefer that word.) These have fantastic grip, which makes them super long-lasting and prevents them from sliding outside my lip border. I always prefer a more grippy formula so I love that they made this choice. The addition of peptides is exciting to me, I always prefer my lip products to have skincare benefits beyond hydration and moisture.

Scent: the website claims these have a citrus scent and a cooling effect. I don‚Äôt smell any citrus but I do notice a strong menthol cooling sensation. So strong that the scent and cooling effect last for 30 minutes before fading. Weirdly, I like it? Normally I hate menthol in lip products but something about this is refreshing and not irritating to me.

Shades (* indicates my favorites):
Emily (clear shimmer)
Marlene (light pink)
